The paper discusses connections between coding-theoretic objects and sparse learning problems, which are typically studied in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses compressed sensing matrices, which are used in numerical analysis (cs.NA), and group testing designs, which are studied in social networks and graph theory (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT, followed by cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.NA, and cs.SI.
